---
// src/pages/commercial/grill-repair/grease-fire-prevention.astro
// Wave 13 — Commercial grill grease fire prevention. Ansul integration, Fire Marshal compliance, PM contracts.
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import CommercialHero from '../../../components/CommercialHero.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE } from '../../../data/branches';

const phone = MAIN_PHONE;
const phoneRaw = MAIN_PHONE.replace(/\D/g, '');
const phoneHref = `tel:+1${phoneRaw}`;
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/commercial/grill-repair/grease-fire-prevention/";

const title = "Commercial Grill Grease Fire Prevention LA | Ansul, Fire Marshal, PM Contracts | $120";
const description = `Commercial outdoor grill grease fire prevention. Wolf Outdoor, Lynx Pro Sear, Twin Eagles, MagiKitch'n. $120.`;

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Restaurant patio grill grease fire risk vs indoor cooking. Higher or lower?",
    a: "Higher per cubic foot of cooking space, but the suppression environment is different. Outdoor grills have more open ventilation (less likely to develop into structure fire from grease ignition), but they also have less standard fire suppression coverage than indoor cooking equipment. California Fire Code (CFC) Chapter 6 and LA County Fire Department local amendments require fire suppression on commercial outdoor grills installed under combustible structures (covered patios, pergolas, awnings) or within proximity of combustible building elements. Open-air installs at unattached patio islands are typically exempt from suppression requirements but still need grease management code compliance.",
  },
  {
    q: "Ansul fire suppression integration. How does the grill connect?",
    a: "Ansul R-102 wet-chemical fire suppression (or equivalent Pyro-Chem, Amerex KP, Buckeye Kitchen Mister) is the standard commercial kitchen fire suppression system. Integration with outdoor commercial grills requires (1) suppression nozzle aimed at the grill cooking surface, (2) gas shut-off valve on the supply line that triggers when suppression activates (cuts gas to the grill instantly), (3) detection link in the hood plenum that triggers the system. Ansul installation and certification is specialty trade (we don't do new Ansul installs); our work integrates with existing Ansul systems by ensuring the grill side functions properly: gas valve responds to suppression trigger, grease management is functional so no grease accumulation triggers a false alarm, etc.",
  },
  {
    q: "LA Fire Marshal annual inspection requirements?",
    a: "LA Fire Marshal annual inspection on commercial cooking equipment includes (1) Ansul or equivalent fire suppression certification (annual), (2) grease management functional verification, (3) grill grease tray cleanliness, (4) drip channel clear, (5) gas shut-off valve operational with suppression integration, (6) burner combustion quality (yellow flame indicates incomplete combustion, fire risk). Failed inspection results in red-tag on the grill (cannot operate) until remediation and re-inspection. We document our service work directly into the LA Fire Marshal compliance file format on PM contracts.",
  },
  {
    q: "Annual PM contract for grease fire prevention. What's included?",
    a: "Standard annual PM contract for commercial outdoor grill grease fire prevention includes (1) quarterly grease management cleaning (drip channel, grease tray, burner cleaning), (2) annual gas shut-off valve operational test (verify Ansul integration), (3) annual burner combustion quality verification, (4) documented service file for HD + Fire Marshal compliance, (5) coordination with Ansul certification annual inspection. Pricing depends on grill count and complexity; single Wolf Outdoor commercial 36-inch with Ansul integration runs $680 to $980 annual. Restaurants with 4+ grease-producing pieces (grill + charbroiler + range + fryer) get bundled multi-equipment PM at 30 to 40 percent volume discount.",
  },
  {
    q: "Insurance coverage on grease fire claims. Documentation required?",
    a: "Restaurant insurance carriers (Cincinnati Insurance, Liberty Mutual restaurants, Travelers commercial, AmTrust restaurants, the major restaurant insurance carriers) require documented annual service on grease-producing equipment for full coverage on grease fire claims. Without documented service, insurance carriers may invoke 'failure to maintain' exclusions on grease fire claims, potentially denying coverage on losses ranging from $50K (kitchen replacement) to $500K+ (structure damage if grease fire spreads). We provide documented service files in the format insurance carriers accept directly. PM contract typically pays for itself in the first prevented insurance dispute.",
  },
  {
    q: "Specific LA installs we serve for grease fire prevention?",
    a: "Restaurant patios across Beverly Hills (Spago Beverly Hills outdoor, Wolfgang Puck at Hotel Bel-Air), West Hollywood (West Hollywood EDITION rooftop, Sunset Tower Hotel pool grill), Santa Monica (Casa del Mar, Shutters on the Beach beach grills), Pasadena (Langham Pasadena terrace), Calabasas (Calamigos Ranch outdoor catering kitchen). Hotel rooftops in DTLA (Hotel Indigo Downtown LA, JW Marriott LA Live), country clubs (Brentwood CC, Riviera CC, Bel-Air CC outdoor cooking stations). Sports venue concessions (LA Memorial Coliseum, Crypto.com Arena outdoor, Dodger Stadium concession kitchens). Catering operations across LA County. We serve all five SoCal counties.",
  },
  {
    q: "What's your warranty?",
    a: "90 days SDAR labor and parts on every repair. Brand component warranties (Wolf Outdoor commercial Middleby, Lynx Pro Sear, Twin Eagles Dometic, MagiKitch'n outdoor Middleby) processed separately. PM contract terms run annual with documented Fire Marshal compliance file. BHGS #A49573, BBB A+ accredited, EPA 608 Universal certified #1346255700410.",
  },
];

const schemaJsons = [
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "LocalBusiness", "@id": canonical + "#business",
    "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair", "url": canonical, "telephone": phone, "priceRange": "$$",
    "openingHoursSpecification": [{ "@type": "OpeningHoursSpecification", "dayOfWeek": ["Monday","Tuesday","Wednesday","Thursday","Friday","Saturday"], "opens": "08:00", "closes": "20:00" }],
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },{ "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },{ "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },{ "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },{ "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" },
    ],
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Service", "@id": canonical + "#service",
    "serviceType": "Commercial Grill Grease Fire Prevention", "name": "Commercial Grill Fire Prevention PM and Compliance Service", "url": canonical,
    "description": "Commercial outdoor grill grease fire prevention service across all five SoCal counties. California Fire Code (CFC) Chapter 6 + LA County Fire Department compliance. Ansul R-102 (Pyro-Chem, Amerex KP, Buckeye Kitchen Mister) fire suppression integration: gas shut-off valve operational test, grease management functional verification, combustion quality verification. Annual PM contracts with documented Fire Marshal + Health Department compliance file. Insurance coverage documentation. Wolf Outdoor commercial, Lynx Pro Sear, Twin Eagles commercial, MagiKitch'n outdoor. LA hospitality cluster: Beverly Hills, WeHo, Santa Monica, Pasadena, hotel rooftops, country clubs, sports venue concessions. $120 commercial diagnostic, applied toward repair. BHGS #A49573, EPA 608 Universal certified #1346255700410.",
    "provider": { "@id": canonical + "#business" },
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },{ "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },{ "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },{ "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },{ "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" },
    ],
    "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "priceSpecification": { "@type": "PriceSpecification", "price": "120.00", "priceCurrency": "USD", "description": "Commercial diagnostic fee, applied toward repair" } },
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({ "@type": "Question", "name": f.q, "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a } })) },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Commercial", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/commercial/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Grill Repair", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/commercial/grill-repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "Grease Fire Prevention", "item": canonical },
    ],
  },
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
<Fragment slot="head-scripts">
  {schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}
</Fragment>

<CommercialHero
  title="Commercial Grill Grease Fire Prevention, PM + Fire Marshal Compliance"
  subtitle={`California Fire Code Chapter 6 + LA County Fire Marshal compliance. Ansul integration, annual PM, insurance documentation. Wolf Outdoor, Lynx Pro Sear, Twin Eagles. $120 commercial. ${phone}`}
  heroImageTitle="Commercial Grill Grease Fire Prevention"
  showBranches={true}
/>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Grease fire prevention service</p>
    <h2>Annual PM contract is much cheaper than red-tag repair plus insurance dispute.</h2>

    <p>Commercial outdoor grill grease fire prevention sits at the intersection of three compliance frameworks. <strong>California Fire Code (CFC) Chapter 6</strong> plus LA County Fire Department local amendments require functional grease management and (where applicable) fire suppression integration. <strong>LA County Department of Public Health</strong> requires functional grease management as part of commercial cooking inspection. <strong>Restaurant insurance carriers</strong> (Cincinnati, Liberty Mutual, Travelers, AmTrust) require documented annual service on grease-producing equipment for full coverage on grease fire claims.</p>

    <p>The work itself: quarterly grease management cleaning (drip channel, grease tray, burner cleaning), annual gas shut-off valve operational test (verifies Ansul R-102 fire suppression integration), annual burner combustion quality verification (yellow flame indicates incomplete combustion, fire risk), documented service file for HD + Fire Marshal compliance. We don't do new Ansul installation (specialty fire-protection trade); we integrate with existing Ansul systems on the grill side.</p>

    <p>Annual PM contract pricing: single Wolf Outdoor commercial 36-inch with Ansul integration runs $680 to $980 annual. Restaurants with 4+ grease-producing pieces (grill + charbroiler + range + fryer) get bundled multi-equipment PM at 30 to 40 percent volume discount.</p>

    <p>$120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. <strong>BHGS #A49573</strong>. <strong>EPA 608 Universal certified #1346255700410</strong>. BBB A+. Phones answered 24/7. Parent: <a href="/commercial/grill-repair/">commercial grill repair</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Compliance framework</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Three compliance angles for commercial grill grease fire prevention.</h2>
    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>California Fire Code (CFC) Chapter 6.</strong> Functional grease management; fire suppression on grills under combustible structures.</li>
      <li><strong>LA County Fire Department local amendments.</strong> Annual inspection, documented service file, gas shut-off valve operational with suppression integration.</li>
      <li><strong>LA County Department of Public Health.</strong> Functional grease management as part of commercial cooking inspection.</li>
      <li><strong>Restaurant insurance carrier requirements.</strong> Documented annual service for full coverage on grease fire claims.</li>
      <li><strong>Ansul R-102 (or equivalent) fire suppression integration.</strong> Gas shut-off valve trigger, detection link in hood plenum, grease accumulation false-alarm prevention.</li>
      <li><strong>Combustion quality verification.</strong> Blue steady flame at full firing; yellow flame indicates fire risk.</li>
      <li><strong>Drip channel and grease tray cleanliness.</strong> Quarterly minimum on commercial duty cycle.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Annual PM contract structure</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Quarterly cleaning + annual compliance verification.</h2>
    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>Quarterly cleaning visits (4 per year).</strong> Drip channel cleaning, grease tray cleaning, burner deep cleaning, surface inspection.</li>
      <li><strong>Annual fire suppression integration test.</strong> Gas shut-off valve operational test, suppression trigger response verification.</li>
      <li><strong>Annual combustion quality verification.</strong> Manometer pressure, flame quality, CO test if available.</li>
      <li><strong>Annual Fire Marshal coordination.</strong> Schedule alignment with annual Fire Marshal inspection, documented service file delivery.</li>
      <li><strong>Annual Health Department documentation.</strong> Service file delivered into HD compliance format.</li>
      <li><strong>Insurance coverage documentation.</strong> Annual service file in carrier-acceptable format.</li>
      <li><strong>Emergency dispatch priority.</strong> PM contract holders jump to front of dispatch queue.</li>
      <li><strong>End-of-season inspection (May).</strong> Per-grill remaining-life estimate.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Honest opinion</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">PM math beats red-tag math, every time.</h2>
    <p>The single highest-leverage move on commercial grill grease fire prevention is annual PM contract with documented compliance file. PM cost: $680 to $980 per grill annual, less with multi-equipment bundle. Alternative: reactive repair when Fire Marshal red-tags the grill, which costs the emergency repair fee ($800 to $2,000), the lost revenue while red-tagged ($5,000 to $20,000 per day on a busy LA hotel patio), the documentation overhead to satisfy Fire Marshal recertification ($1,000 to $3,000 in our service time), and the downstream insurance dispute risk if any grease incident occurred during non-compliant operation (potentially $50K to $500K). The math is obvious. We recommend PM because it's what we'd do for our own restaurant.</p>
  </div>
</section>

